{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix preamble index configuration for CFRA in NR MAC UE\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE MAC layer had incorrect behavior when configuring preamble indices for Contention-Free Random Access (CFRA). The issue occurred because the preamble selection logic was overwriting pre-configured CFRA preamble indices with randomly selected ones.\n\nThis happened due to missing checks for the CFRA flag (`ra->cfra`) in the `ra_preambles_config` function, causing the code to apply contention-based RA preamble selection even for CFRA procedures where the preamble index should remain fixed as configured by RRC.\n\nThe bug was particularly evident when using 2-step RACH configurations where the gNB assigns specific preamble indices for CFRA, but the UE was selecting different random preambles instead.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ra_procedures.c`: Added CFRA flag checks to prevent overwriting configured preamble indices\n- Updated preamble index boundary check from 63 to 255 to align with 3GPP specifications\n- Added explanatory comments for clarity on CFRA vs CBRA handling\n\n"
}